    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To use the nearest neighbor method manually, you start at your depot and always choose the next unvisited location that is closest to your current position. You repeat this until all 12 stops are visited, then connect back to the depot to close the loop.\n\nWhile this is simple to follow, it can sometimes produce a route that is not the globally optimal one because it doesn't look ahead at future stops. For a small problem like 12 locations, you can manually run the algorithm or use a simple spreadsheet to calculate distances and swap segments if you want to refine the result.\n\nFor example, if your first stop is location A, you would calculate the distance from the depot to A, then from A to the nearest remaining location, and so on, until the last stop is reached. This greedy approach is often close enough to the best route for small routes and requires no complex programming.",
      "source": "target",
